Text.SourceString: I thought a delightful, home-cooked meal would be just the ticket to fuel your farming adventures today, my love.//Please enjoy!
Text.LocalizedString: I thought a delightful, home-cooked meal would be just the ticket to fuel your farming adventures today, my love.//Please enjoy!

Text.SourceString: I'm not technically a cook, but I dabbled a bit in culinary arts back in my university days.//<portrait=blushing>I hope this meal is up to your standard, my darling.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm not technically a cook, but I dabbled a bit in culinary arts back in my university days.//<portrait=blushing>I hope this meal is up to your standard, my darling.

Text.SourceString: What I've come to love the most about our home is that it's truly ours...and it's just so cute, don't you agree?
Text.LocalizedString: What I've come to love the most about our home is that it's truly ours...and it's just so cute, don't you agree?

Text.SourceString: Never in my wildest dreams did I imagine I would end up living here...//<portrait=blushing>All those blissful Summer days we spent together as children certainly foreshadowed my love for this place.
Text.LocalizedString: Never in my wildest dreams did I imagine I would end up living here...//<portrait=blushing>All those blissful Summer days we spent together as children certainly foreshadowed my love for this place.

Text.SourceString: I knew then that I'd love it here, and I was absolutely right.
Text.LocalizedString: I knew then that I'd love it here, and I was absolutely right.

Text.SourceString: There is something immensely rewarding about cultivating our own meals.//They have a freshness that's unmatched by any five-star restaurant I've dined at.
Text.LocalizedString: There is something immensely rewarding about cultivating our own meals.//They have a freshness that's unmatched by any five-star restaurant I've dined at.

Text.SourceString: It's been a culinary revelation, to say the least.
Text.LocalizedString: It's been a culinary revelation, to say the least.

Text.SourceString: I've spent practically my whole life by the sea...the salty air, the sound of waves, it's lovely.//But here, there's a different kind of bliss.
Text.LocalizedString: I've spent practically my whole life by the sea...the salty air, the sound of waves, it's lovely.//But here, there's a different kind of bliss.

Text.SourceString: What are your plans for today, darling?
Text.LocalizedString: What are your plans for today, darling?

Text.SourceString: Can I watch you work outside?
Text.LocalizedString: Can I watch you work outside?

Text.SourceString: The view of our farm from here is simply exquisite...
Text.LocalizedString: The view of our farm from here is simply exquisite...

Text.SourceString: Perhaps I'll paint today.//Or maybe I'll just relax with some TV. It feels like one of those days.
Text.LocalizedString: Perhaps I'll paint today.//Or maybe I'll just relax with some TV. It feels like one of those days.

Text.SourceString: I think I'll take a stroll into town today, perhaps pick up some groceries for the house.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I'll take a stroll into town today, perhaps pick up some groceries for the house.

Text.SourceString: Darling, your efforts on our farm never cease to amaze me. You truly have a gift.
Text.LocalizedString: Darling, your efforts on our farm never cease to amaze me. You truly have a gift.

Text.SourceString: You look stunning in that outfit, my love.
Text.LocalizedString: You look stunning in that outfit, my love.

Text.SourceString: I love you, darling. Please don't ever forget that.
Text.LocalizedString: I love you, darling. Please don't ever forget that.

Text.SourceString: You're the most important thing in my life.
Text.LocalizedString: You're the most important thing in my life.

Text.SourceString: I'm thinking of making a short trip to the villa later this week. Let some fresh air in, perhaps.//<portrait=normal>We have art pieces in there that need a good airing to prevent mold, you see.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm thinking of making a short trip to the villa later this week. Let some fresh air in, perhaps.//<portrait=normal>We have art pieces in there that need a good airing to prevent mold, you see.

Text.SourceString: I gave our home a bit of a tidy.//<portrait=surprised>Surprisingly, I found the process quite enjoyable.
Text.LocalizedString: I gave our home a bit of a tidy.//<portrait=surprised>Surprisingly, I found the process quite enjoyable.

Text.SourceString: In here, each morning I wake to the crowing of the rooster, and each night I drift off to the chorus of crickets.// It’s quite a change of pace, but a welcome one, indeed.
Text.LocalizedString: In here, each morning I wake to the crowing of the rooster, and each night I drift off to the chorus of crickets.// It’s quite a change of pace, but a welcome one, indeed.

Text.SourceString: I remember when the beach was just a stone's throw away from my old home.//Well, the longer trek now makes me appreciate it even more.
Text.LocalizedString: I remember when the beach was just a stone's throw away from my old home.//Well, the longer trek now makes me appreciate it even more.

Text.SourceString: It's a bit of a hike to get to the beach from our home, but the sound of the waves and the smell of the salty air...oh, it's all worth it!
Text.LocalizedString: It's a bit of a hike to get to the beach from our home, but the sound of the waves and the smell of the salty air...oh, it's all worth it!

Text.SourceString: We might need to invest in a charming beach picnic basket, darling.
Text.LocalizedString: We might need to invest in a charming beach picnic basket, darling.

Text.SourceString: Are you accompanying me here, darling?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you accompanying me here, darling?

Text.SourceString: I think I'll head home soon.//I must admit, I'm feeling a little tired.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I'll head home soon.//I must admit, I'm feeling a little tired.

Text.SourceString: Returning here... this house remains the same since I was <NpcName>Valentina</>'s age.//<portrait=annoyed>The only difference is that it's now empty...
Text.LocalizedString: Returning here... this house remains the same since I was <NpcName>Valentina</>'s age.//<portrait=annoyed>The only difference is that it's now empty...

Text.SourceString: I've left some food in the refrigerator for <NpcName>Lily</>, just in case she decides to drop by. It's her surprise treat!//<portrait=normal>She does enjoy her alone time here.
Text.LocalizedString: I've left some food in the refrigerator for <NpcName>Lily</>, just in case she decides to drop by. It's her surprise treat!//<portrait=normal>She does enjoy her alone time here.

Text.SourceString: It still tugs at my heart each time I pass by my parents' room.//My father's absence...it's a void I'm unable to fill.
Text.LocalizedString: It still tugs at my heart each time I pass by my parents' room.//My father's absence...it's a void I'm unable to fill.

Text.SourceString: *Sigh*
Text.LocalizedString: *Sigh*

Text.SourceString: Please, make yourself at home, my love.//This, after all, is as much your home as it is mine.
Text.LocalizedString: Please, make yourself at home, my love.//This, after all, is as much your home as it is mine.

Text.SourceString: Oh, it's raining outside. Perhaps we could spend the day indoors?//<portrait=happy>We could make some banana fritters and indulge in a TV marathon, darling.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, it's raining outside. Perhaps we could spend the day indoors?//<portrait=happy>We could make some banana fritters and indulge in a TV marathon, darling.

Text.SourceString: This snowfall just makes me want to burrow under the covers all day. Care to join me, darling?
Text.LocalizedString: This snowfall just makes me want to burrow under the covers all day. Care to join me, darling?

Text.SourceString: Oh, it's raining outside. Perhaps we could spend the day indoors?//<portrait=happy>We could make some banana fritters and indulge in a TV marathon, darling.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, it's raining outside. Perhaps we could spend the day indoors?//<portrait=happy>We could make some banana fritters and indulge in a TV marathon, darling.

Text.SourceString: Falling asleep with my windows open is the best. The sound of the nature is so relaxing.
Text.LocalizedString: Falling asleep with my windows open is the best. The sound of the nature is so relaxing.

Text.SourceString: You know, living alone wasn't as bad as I thought it would be.
Text.LocalizedString: You know, living alone wasn't as bad as I thought it would be.

Text.SourceString: But this is much better, of course. I didn't know what I was missing.
Text.LocalizedString: But this is much better, of course. I didn't know what I was missing.

Text.SourceString: It's strawberry season! Oh, I would love to have a picnic in our very own strawberry patch.
Text.LocalizedString: It's strawberry season! Oh, I would love to have a picnic in our very own strawberry patch.

Text.SourceString: What better way to spend the afternoon than toting around a basketful of berries and fresh flowers?
Text.LocalizedString: What better way to spend the afternoon than toting around a basketful of berries and fresh flowers?

Text.SourceString: It’s blueberry season! Oh, I would love to have a picnic in our very own blueberry patch.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s blueberry season! Oh, I would love to have a picnic in our very own blueberry patch.

Text.SourceString: What better way to spend the afternoon than toting around a basketful of berries and fresh flowers?
Text.LocalizedString: What better way to spend the afternoon than toting around a basketful of berries and fresh flowers?

Text.SourceString: It’s cranberry season!  Oh, I would love to have a picnic in our very own cranberry patch.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s cranberry season!  Oh, I would love to have a picnic in our very own cranberry patch.

Text.SourceString: What better way to spend the afternoon than toting around a basketful of berries and fresh flowers?
Text.LocalizedString: What better way to spend the afternoon than toting around a basketful of berries and fresh flowers?

Text.SourceString: Happy Sunday to you, my darling!
Text.LocalizedString: Happy Sunday to you, my darling!

Text.SourceString: I get confused when people ask me where I’m from. Coral Island is definitely home to me, so I always tell them that.
Text.LocalizedString: I get confused when people ask me where I’m from. Coral Island is definitely home to me, so I always tell them that.

Text.SourceString: Even though I was born here, darling, Mother hails from an entirely different corner of the world.//Hence, the conundrum...am I truly a Coral Island native?
Text.LocalizedString: Even though I was born here, darling, Mother hails from an entirely different corner of the world.//Hence, the conundrum...am I truly a Coral Island native?

Text.SourceString: I must confess, there were times growing up when I felt as though I didn't quite match my own reflection in the family portrait.//An artist with mismatched paint, if you will.
Text.LocalizedString: I must confess, there were times growing up when I felt as though I didn't quite match my own reflection in the family portrait.//An artist with mismatched paint, if you will.

Text.SourceString: But over the years, I've learned that my unique blend is not a sign of not fitting in, but rather a badge of honor...a testament to the rich tapestry of my existence.//<portrait=happy>After all, what's life without a little spice?
Text.LocalizedString: But over the years, I've learned that my unique blend is not a sign of not fitting in, but rather a badge of honor...a testament to the rich tapestry of my existence.//<portrait=happy>After all, what's life without a little spice?

Text.SourceString: Growing up, I often felt like an amalgam of my parents, not quite mirroring either of them.//It made me feel somewhat out of place.
Text.LocalizedString: Growing up, I often felt like an amalgam of my parents, not quite mirroring either of them.//It made me feel somewhat out of place.

Text.SourceString: Thankfully, none of the people here ever made me feel like my appearance matters too much.//Family gatherings, on the other hand... Let's just say my cousins had a knack for reminding me of my uniqueness.
Text.LocalizedString: Thankfully, none of the people here ever made me feel like my appearance matters too much.//Family gatherings, on the other hand... Let's just say my cousins had a knack for reminding me of my uniqueness.

Text.SourceString: Being caught between two families, two cultures, has always lent a certain...intrigue to my life.//When I was with my mom's side, they would look at me and see Father.//With all the blondes, I was the only one with black hair.
Text.LocalizedString: Being caught between two families, two cultures, has always lent a certain...intrigue to my life.//When I was with my mom's side, they would look at me and see Father.//With all the blondes, I was the only one with black hair.

Text.SourceString: Then with Father's family, they would look at me and see Mother.//<portrait=normal>I was like her mirror in how I moved and behaved.
Text.LocalizedString: Then with Father's family, they would look at me and see Mother.//<portrait=normal>I was like her mirror in how I moved and behaved.

Text.SourceString: I’m so excited for Summer, darl. It’ll be so much fun!//<portrait=surprised>The food, the swimming, the beach – everything!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m so excited for Summer, darl. It’ll be so much fun!//<portrait=surprised>The food, the swimming, the beach – everything!

Text.SourceString: I tried going into the ocean the other day, and it was still too cold!//<portrait=concerned>Maybe I need to wait a few more days…
Text.LocalizedString: I tried going into the ocean the other day, and it was still too cold!//<portrait=concerned>Maybe I need to wait a few more days…

Text.SourceString: Oh, darl, it’s finally, finally getting warmer. I can feel the Summer vibes just around the corner!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, darl, it’s finally, finally getting warmer. I can feel the Summer vibes just around the corner!

Text.SourceString: I wonder what <NPCName>Suki</> is up to. Frantically cleaning the inn, probably.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder what <NPCName>Suki</> is up to. Frantically cleaning the inn, probably.

Text.SourceString: Father was the one who taught me how to surf and sail. Well…not personally. He was too busy for that.//But he was the one pushing for lessons and camps.
Text.LocalizedString: Father was the one who taught me how to surf and sail. Well…not personally. He was too busy for that.//But he was the one pushing for lessons and camps.

Text.SourceString: The Beach Cleanup Festival is the main reason I love Summer so much.
Text.LocalizedString: The Beach Cleanup Festival is the main reason I love Summer so much.

Text.SourceString: What should I do today?//The cold weather makes me lazy.
Text.LocalizedString: What should I do today?//The cold weather makes me lazy.

Text.SourceString: There’s something really beautiful about the beach in Winter, isn’t there?
Text.LocalizedString: There’s something really beautiful about the beach in Winter, isn’t there?

Text.SourceString: Oh, darling, how do you stay so active in Winter? It’s so cold!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, darling, how do you stay so active in Winter? It’s so cold!

Text.SourceString: I can’t wait for the New Year’s Eve Festival!//<portrait=normal>I definitely missed it when I moved away.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t wait for the New Year’s Eve Festival!//<portrait=normal>I definitely missed it when I moved away.

Text.SourceString: We need to keep hydrated, always. Especially in Winter, when it’s dry like this.
Text.LocalizedString: We need to keep hydrated, always. Especially in Winter, when it’s dry like this.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Bree’s</> parties are always so much fun, aren’t they? Nowhere near as much fun as Mother’s, of course. Too bad you haven’t been to any.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Bree’s</> parties are always so much fun, aren’t they? Nowhere near as much fun as Mother’s, of course. Too bad you haven’t been to any.

Text.SourceString: I’m so tempted to spend the Winter somewhere warmer.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m so tempted to spend the Winter somewhere warmer.

Text.SourceString: Ah, the wind is nice and breezy today!
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, the wind is nice and breezy today!

Text.SourceString: We got just what we needed.
Text.LocalizedString: We got just what we needed.

Text.SourceString: This may sound a bit silly, but I’m curious about the forest. I heard there are monsters in the cavern.
Text.LocalizedString: This may sound a bit silly, but I’m curious about the forest. I heard there are monsters in the cavern.

Text.SourceString: I’m afraid if I go to the forest alone, I might get lost and run into one of those monsters.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m afraid if I go to the forest alone, I might get lost and run into one of those monsters.

Text.SourceString: Ha ha ha. Silly, I know.
Text.LocalizedString: Ha ha ha. Silly, I know.

Text.SourceString: The leaves are solid brown now. It’s a sign the trees will start losing leaves soon.
Text.LocalizedString: The leaves are solid brown now. It’s a sign the trees will start losing leaves soon.

Text.SourceString: The weather has definitely changed, but not enough to need a sweater.//I’m fine, thanks for asking.
Text.LocalizedString: The weather has definitely changed, but not enough to need a sweater.//I’m fine, thanks for asking.

Text.SourceString: I got my party-planning gene from Mother.//She’d invite everybody on the island for my birthday.
Text.LocalizedString: I got my party-planning gene from Mother.//She’d invite everybody on the island for my birthday.

Text.SourceString: I never really understood why, because honestly, to me, it was more tiring than anything. And I always had to wear some itchy dress. I hated those. The parties, though – They were out of this world.
Text.LocalizedString: I never really understood why, because honestly, to me, it was more tiring than anything. And I always had to wear some itchy dress. I hated those. The parties, though – They were out of this world.

Text.SourceString: Oh my! Was that thunder I just heard?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh my! Was that thunder I just heard?

Text.SourceString: Humph. Oh well… The rain is only water, right? So what if it’s a little muddy and thundery?
Text.LocalizedString: Humph. Oh well… The rain is only water, right? So what if it’s a little muddy and thundery?

Text.SourceString: Oh, this rain isn’t going to stop me from leaving my house.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, this rain isn’t going to stop me from leaving my house.

Text.SourceString: It’s just a little bit of water.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s just a little bit of water.

Text.SourceString: This place hasn’t changed. I love it.
Text.LocalizedString: This place hasn’t changed. I love it.

Text.SourceString: Father used to bring me here after hours to get a treat.
Text.LocalizedString: Father used to bring me here after hours to get a treat.

Text.SourceString: I suppose it doesn’t matter how far away I go. I’ll always belong here…//Close to Father.
Text.LocalizedString: I suppose it doesn’t matter how far away I go. I’ll always belong here…//Close to Father.

Text.SourceString: I don’t see kids building elaborate sandcastles anymore.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t see kids building elaborate sandcastles anymore.

Text.SourceString: I suppose it may be a different era now.
Text.LocalizedString: I suppose it may be a different era now.

Text.SourceString: I don’t need most of the things here. My family has so much unnecessary stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t need most of the things here. My family has so much unnecessary stuff.

Text.SourceString: This stuff is never used. It’s probably bored, sitting around with nobody paying attention to it.
Text.LocalizedString: This stuff is never used. It’s probably bored, sitting around with nobody paying attention to it.

Text.SourceString: I learned to sail a long time ago, when I was <NPCName>Valentina’s</> age. Father sent me to a Summer camp where I also learned to scuba dive.
Text.LocalizedString: I learned to sail a long time ago, when I was <NPCName>Valentina’s</> age. Father sent me to a Summer camp where I also learned to scuba dive.

Text.SourceString: I’m not a big diver, but it did add some heft to my college application.//And it comes in handy for conversation at cocktail parties. So, I’m grateful.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not a big diver, but it did add some heft to my college application.//And it comes in handy for conversation at cocktail parties. So, I’m grateful.

Text.SourceString: This town is like a cute little time capsule.//Hasn’t changed much since I left. Without a doubt, it carries a lot of memories.
Text.LocalizedString: This town is like a cute little time capsule.//Hasn’t changed much since I left. Without a doubt, it carries a lot of memories.

Text.SourceString: Hmm… Carries some bad memories too, though.//So, not a very cute time capsule, I suppose.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… Carries some bad memories too, though.//So, not a very cute time capsule, I suppose.

Text.SourceString: My parents collected antiques from different eras.//That’s how they bonded. Over old, musty decor. Shocking!
Text.LocalizedString: My parents collected antiques from different eras.//That’s how they bonded. Over old, musty decor. Shocking!

Text.SourceString: Who am I kidding? I love it too! I love old, musty decor. Ha ha.
Text.LocalizedString: Who am I kidding? I love it too! I love old, musty decor. Ha ha.

Text.SourceString: I get why people like this place.//It’s so homey here…
Text.LocalizedString: I get why people like this place.//It’s so homey here…

Text.SourceString: The family that used to take care of the farm for us always had the same dinner here, for years.
Text.LocalizedString: The family that used to take care of the farm for us always had the same dinner here, for years.

Text.SourceString: I can’t remember if I turned my TV off before coming here.//Yeah, I did.//Wait… No… Never mind.//<portrait=normal>Maybe I should call it a night. Yeah.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t remember if I turned my TV off before coming here.//Yeah, I did.//Wait… No… Never mind.//<portrait=normal>Maybe I should call it a night. Yeah.

Text.SourceString: What do you think about this house?//Do you like it? Should I repaint the walls?
Text.LocalizedString: What do you think about this house?//Do you like it? Should I repaint the walls?

Text.SourceString: The flowers here are beautiful. It makes me feel like a fairy when I’m in this garden.
Text.LocalizedString: The flowers here are beautiful. It makes me feel like a fairy when I’m in this garden.

Text.SourceString: I spoke to <NpcName>Raj</> the other day.//They sure know a lot about coffee. I don’t think I understood half the things they said.
Text.LocalizedString: I spoke to <NpcName>Raj</> the other day.//They sure know a lot about coffee. I don’t think I understood half the things they said.

Text.SourceString: Care to join us, <PlayerName>$Player</>?//<NpcName>Lily</> and I are just catching up.
Text.LocalizedString: Care to join us, <PlayerName>$Player</>?//<NpcName>Lily</> and I are just catching up.

Text.SourceString: It’s a bit too cold to keep the windows open now.//<portrait=concerned>The ocean wind is strong.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a bit too cold to keep the windows open now.//<portrait=concerned>The ocean wind is strong.

Text.SourceString: Should we head to bed soon, my love?
Text.LocalizedString: Should we head to bed soon, my love?

Text.SourceString: I bumped into the Mayor earlier today, and he was asking about you.//<portrait=normal>Isn't he kind?
Text.LocalizedString: I bumped into the Mayor earlier today, and he was asking about you.//<portrait=normal>Isn't he kind?

Text.SourceString: I think I'll pay a visit to <NpcName>Suki</> tomorrow, darling. I miss her so much.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I'll pay a visit to <NpcName>Suki</> tomorrow, darling. I miss her so much.

Text.SourceString: As her friend, I'm glad <NpcName>Suki</>'s getting along well with <NpcName>Antonio</>.//It was tough when they went through their divorce, she shed so many tears...but deep down, she knew it was the right decision.
Text.LocalizedString: As her friend, I'm glad <NpcName>Suki</>'s getting along well with <NpcName>Antonio</>.//It was tough when they went through their divorce, she shed so many tears...but deep down, she knew it was the right decision.

Text.SourceString: How was your day today, darling? You seem like you could use a relaxing massage.
Text.LocalizedString: How was your day today, darling? You seem like you could use a relaxing massage.

Text.SourceString: I've been considering ordering some paints online.//I'm running low on violet, and I have a new masterpiece in mind.
Text.LocalizedString: I've been considering ordering some paints online.//I'm running low on violet, and I have a new masterpiece in mind.

Text.SourceString: What time should we head to the Cherry Blossom Festival tomorrow, darling?
Text.LocalizedString: What time should we head to the Cherry Blossom Festival tomorrow, darling?

Text.SourceString: I'm so excited to attend the Pet Day with you tomorrow, my love.//Are we planning to enter any contests?
Text.LocalizedString: I'm so excited to attend the Pet Day with you tomorrow, my love.//Are we planning to enter any contests?

Text.SourceString: Let's make sure to get a good night's rest tonight, darling.//We have a big clean-up day ahead of us tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: Let's make sure to get a good night's rest tonight, darling.//We have a big clean-up day ahead of us tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: Have you thought about joining the swimming contest?//You'd be a splash-tastic champion, no doubt!
Text.LocalizedString: Have you thought about joining the swimming contest?//You'd be a splash-tastic champion, no doubt!

Text.SourceString: I'm going to arrive early at the Harvest Festival tomorrow, darling.//<portrait=concerned>I promised <NpcName>Millie</> I'd help out with the signage. I'll meet you there, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: I'm going to arrive early at the Harvest Festival tomorrow, darling.//<portrait=concerned>I promised <NpcName>Millie</> I'd help out with the signage. I'll meet you there, okay?

Text.SourceString: Oh wow! The Spooky Festival is tomorrow! I need to find my costume ASAP!//I'm super excited!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh wow! The Spooky Festival is tomorrow! I need to find my costume ASAP!//I'm super excited!

Text.SourceString: I had this wild dream last night!//You, yes, YOU, were out there farming, while I was sitting on our porch.//Suddenly, a colossal crop sprouted legs and started chasing you.
Text.LocalizedString: I had this wild dream last night!//You, yes, YOU, were out there farming, while I was sitting on our porch.//Suddenly, a colossal crop sprouted legs and started chasing you.

Text.SourceString: I woke up, my heart pounding like crazy.
Text.LocalizedString: I woke up, my heart pounding like crazy.
